item.title: big quakes recently
item.description: 21:31 Saturday 30 May 2015 JST Not that no one else has noticed, but we’ve had a few big earthquakes in Japan recently, most recently at 8:34pm. It felt like a 3 or 4 in The Pink Cow, but it was a 5 out in the water. Fortunately, it had a depth of hundreds of miles, so no tsunami. 09:30 Sunday 31 May 2015 JST Crud I forgot to upload the image snagged from jma earthquake map
